    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-09-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-09-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="216"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d216">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/2762½</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-09-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">17 September, 1918</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: It occurs to me to request you
                    to make pointed inquiry of the British, French, and Italian governments as to
                    what the so-called Allied Military Council at Vladivostok is, of <pb facs="0432"
                        n="386" xml:id="pg_386"/> whom it is composed, and by whose authority it was
                    formed and is undertaking to act, intimating at the same time that we recognize
                    the authority of no such body and would be very glad to have the situation at
                    Vladivostok cleared of unnecessary complications.</p>
                <p>Cordially and faithfully yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Woodrow Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
